parameter.description:
Specifies the date and time, when the GPS scan last completed successfully.
{{template|FAP-GPS-RESET}}
The values for {{param|LockedLatitude}}, {{param|LockedLongitude}} and {{param|NumberOfSatellites}} correspond to this time. If a scan has never succeeded before, the value will be the Unknown Time value, as defined in {{bibref|TR-106|Section 3.2}}.

The number of satellites that were locked during the test execution. The greater the number of satellites the better the precision of the results.
{{template|FAP-GPS-RESET}}
If a scan has never succeeded before, the value 0 is reported.

The value is {{true}} if the timing synchronization is good,
otherwise it is {{false}}. After a reboot the value is {{false}}
until the timing is synchronized again.

object.description:
This object contains parameters for the configuration of the Assisted
Global Positioning System (A-GPS) server. See also
{{bibref|3GPP-TS.25.171|Section 3.2}}
